<subSubSection id="F7D86578FFB41B03FDD3FAE103E243D2" pageId="10" pageNumber="160" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="BF7D36F3FFB41B03FDD3FAE103E243D2" blockId="10.[457,1853,1058,1508]" pageId="10" pageNumber="160">
This Australian ladybeetle was introduced into 
<collectingCountry id="C7D57663FFB41B03FAA2FAE102E7434A" box="[1400,1505,1364,1404]" name="Guam" pageId="10" pageNumber="160">Guam</collectingCountry>
from Honolulu in 1926 to combat the cottony cushion scale. In 1936 both were scarce, and only 
<specimenCount id="A9C4FD7AFFB41B03FE13FA0E05B543D2" box="[457,691,1467,1508]" pageId="10" pageNumber="160" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
of the ladybeetle was obtained.
</paragraph>
